
# Networking Basics

## What is Networking?

Networking is the process of connecting devices so they can communicate and exchange data. Networks can range from small home networks to the global Internet.

## Types of Networks

### LAN (Local Area Network)
A LAN connects devices within a limited area such as a home, school, or office.

### WAN (Wide Area Network)
A WAN connects devices over large geographical distances. The Internet is the largest WAN.

## IP Address

An IP address is a logical address used to identify a device on a network.

Example:
192.168.1.10

## MAC Address

A MAC address is a unique physical identifier assigned to a network interface.

Example:
00:1A:2B:3C:4D:5E

## Router

A router connects different networks and forwards packets between them.

## Switch

A switch connects devices within the same local network and uses MAC addresses to forward data.

## Key Learning

Networking enables communication between devices. IP addresses identify devices across networks, while MAC addresses identify devices within a local network.
